{'answer': 'LangChain **agents** are a pre-built way to build **LLM-powered applications that can decide what to do next and use tools to get it done**.\n\nIn the LangChain docs, agents are described in the context of LangChain providing a **“pre-built agent architecture and integrations for any model or tool — so you can build agents that adapt as fast as the ecosystem evolves”**. LangChain is positioned as “the easiest way to start building agents and applications powered by LLMs,” with built-in model/tool integrations to get started quickly. LangChain agents are also **built on top of LangGraph**, which provides capabilities like **durable execution, streaming, human-in-the-loop, and persistence** (you don’t need to learn LangGraph for basic LangChain agent usage).  \nSources: LangChain Agents overview page and LangChain overview docs: https: //python.langchain.com/oss/python/langchain/agents and https://python.langchain.com/oss/python/langchain/overview (same text is also shown in the install/overview content retrieved: https://python.langchain.com/oss/python/langchain/install)\n\nIf you tell me what you’re trying to build (chatbot, research assistant, support automation, etc.), I can point you to the most relevant agent pattern in the docs.', 'context': []}